\text{If} \space m^2=(a+1)^3-a^3\text{ where}\space m,a\in\mathbb{N} \implies \exists c,d \in\mathbb{N}\space \text{ such that}\space m=c^2+d^2.
\rm(1)\quad 2\ m - 1  = 3\ j^2,\  2\ m + 1 = k^2\ \Rightarrow\ k^2 - 3\ j^2 = 2\ \Rightarrow\ k^2 \equiv -1\pmod 3\ \Rightarrow\Leftarrow
m^2 = (a+1)^3 - a^3 = 3a^2+3a+1
